&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(247, 25, 99);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SOBRE A VTEX&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;0&quot; data-end=&quot;502&quot;&gt;VTEX é a plataforma de comércio completa que proporciona mais eficiência e menos manutenção para organizações que buscam fazer investimentos mais inteligentes em TI e modernizar sua estrutura de tecnologia. Através da nossa abordagem pragmática, capacitamos marcas, distribuidores e varejistas com uma flexibilidade incomparável e soluções abrangentes, permitindo que invistam apenas no que oferece uma vantagem clara para o negócio e aumenta a lucratividade.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;504&quot; data-end=&quot;750&quot;&gt;A VTEX é confiada por 2.400 clientes globais B2C e B2B, incluindo Carrefour, Colgate, Motorola, Sony, Stanley Black &amp;amp; Decker e Whirlpool, operando 3.400 lojas online ativas em 43 países (dados do ano fiscal encerrado em 31 de dezembro de 2024).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;752&quot; data-end=&quot;1201&quot;&gt;Fundada no ano 2000, a VTEX tem uma trajetória de crescimento imbatível. Desafiando todas as probabilidades, estamos liderando a indústria de alta tecnologia e nos posicionando acima de gigantes do mercado. Estamos construindo um futuro extraordinário com mais de 1.300 colaboradores distribuídos por 25 localidades em 16 países da América Latina, América do Norte, Europa e Ásia. Para mais informações, visite &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.vtex.com&quot; target=&quot;_new&quot; data-start=&quot;1163&quot; data-end=&quot;1198&quot;&gt;www.vtex.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1203&quot; data-end=&quot;1376&quot; data-is-last-node=&quot;&quot; data-is-only-node=&quot;&quot;&gt;Na VTEX, você trabalhará em um ambiente dinâmico e desafiador, colaborando com colegas incríveis. Se você tem força individual, junte-se a nós e, juntos, seremos imparáveis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(247, 25, 99);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INCLUSÃO E ACESSIBILIDADE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Na VTEX, valorizamos a diversidade em todas as suas formas e acreditamos que a inclusão é essencial para o nosso sucesso. Esta vaga é afirmativa para pessoas com deficiência (PCD) como parte do nosso compromisso em promover um ambiente de trabalho diverso e inclusivo. Acreditamos na geração de oportunidades como ferramenta de mudança e estamos focados em encontrar talentos diversos para nossos times! &amp;nbsp;Estamos comprometidos em adaptar nossas instalações e ferramentas para garantir a acessibilidade de todos os nossos colaboradores, bem como dos candidatos do processo seletivo. Se você precisar de alguma adequação especial para participar do nosso processo seletivo, por favor, nos informe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(247, 25, 99);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Principais áreas que recrutamos:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Financeiro&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recursos Humanos&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Jurídico&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tecnologia&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essa é nosso banco de talentos de Diversidade, focado em Inclusão de Pessoas com Deficiência. Nosso time de Recrutamento está constantemente revisando os currículos que chegarem por aqui, e quando identificamos uma ótima oportunidade, entramos em contato com as pessoas para que elas participem do nosso processo de recrutamento.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(247, 25, 99);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quem pode se inscrever?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Todas as pessoas com deficiência podem se inscrever nessa página e em qualquer outra vaga na nossa página de carreiras. Aqui, seu perfil será revisado e, se houver compatibilidade, encaminhado para áreas nas quais estamos contratando. Caso você não se identifique como uma pessoa com deficiência, confira nossas outras oportunidades na&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(247, 25, 99

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Connecting enterprise teams to scalable commerce solutions&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Focused on enterprise engagement and digital transformation initiatives&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Demand Generation Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Demand Generation team is responsible for creating predictable, scalable pipeline and accelerating revenue growth by turning market awareness into qualified opportunities. The team drives integrated campaigns, account-based programs, outbound prospecting initiatives, and full-funnel execution in close partnership with Sales. Success in this function is measured by the ability to create meaningful sales conversations, generate qualified meetings, meet quarterly&amp;nbsp; opportunity quota, and consistently contribute to pipeline growth.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Business and Engagement Development Specialist &lt;/strong&gt;on the Demand Generation team, you will be responsible for creating qualified pipeline through strategic outbound prospecting, business relationship development, and high-impact follow-up across target accounts. This is a true hunter role focused on opening doors, building momentum within accounts, and creating sales opportunities through a combination of modern outbound tactics and traditional relationship-building skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate brings strong outbound sales experience, is confident working across multiple ICPs and verticals, has a solid understanding of the ecommerce and digital commerce industry, and understands how to build a book of business over time.This person knows how to generate traction through cold outreach, thoughtful persistence, account research, referrals, event networking, and strong follow-up discipline. They are highly accountable, metrics-driven, and bring a proven track record of meeting and exceeding KPI expectations. The right person for this role has an outgoing, go-getter personality, thrives in the trenches, and knows how to turn hustle, persistence, and strong business relationship instincts into pipeline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will also support event-related business development efforts and must be comfortable traveling locally and nationally for trade shows, field events, meetings, and prospect engagement.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outbound Pipeline Creation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own outbound prospecting efforts across target accounts, segments, ICPs, and verticals to generate qualified sales opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build account penetration strategies that identify key stakeholders, buying groups, whitespace, and business needs within named accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute high-quality outbound outreach across phone, email, LinkedIn, events, referrals, and other channels to create meaningful sales conversations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personalize messaging based on business context, market signals, vertical challenges, role-specific pain points, and account research.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build momentum within accounts through consistent follow-up, relationship development, and strategic persistence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor market momentum across target accounts and engage at the right time with the right persona based on buying signals, business changes, account activity, and market movement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Relationship Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish early-stage relationships with the right personas within target accounts and develop trust through relevant, informed outreach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the development of a strong book of business by cr

&lt;h2&gt;About the team&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div&gt;The Commerce Engineer team is the support and engine of the VTEX Sales Team. The team seeks to guide and find scalable solutions for our potential customers. The team is trained and prepared to define the project scope, technical proposal, and pricing to reinforce the Sales team approach.Your main responsibilities will include:&lt;br&gt;Build and maintain strong, strategic relationships with large enterprise clients, ensuring consistent and high-level communication.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*This role requires you to be based in Barcelona, and to attend the office 4 days a week (Monday–Thursday), with remote work on Fridays.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Your main responsibilities will include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deeply understand client needs, proposing tailored projects and solutions that drive their business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively monitor the use of our products and services, identifying areas for improvement and value creation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a trusted advisor, guiding clients in adopting best practices to maximize the return on VTEX solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify upsell opportunities and new projects, directly contributing to revenue growth and increased GMV within the portfolio.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop performance-driven strategies to help clients sell more and sell better.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anticipate churn risks, acting swiftly and empathetically to reverse critical situations with personalized action plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the expansion of Annual Contract Value (ACV), from qualifying leads to closing long-term agreements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up to date on our product roadmap and complete relevant certifications to support your growth within VTEX.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Required Skills &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid experience in Customer Success, Account Management, or related areas, especially working with Enterprise (Tier 1) clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record in consultative account management, with a focus on customer retention, revenue expansion (upsell/cross-sell), and long-term success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of churn reduction strategies and customer engagement tactics throughout the client lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to engage with stakeholders at all levels, including C-level executives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills, with the ability to interpret key performance metrics (e.g., NPS, churn rate, GMV, ACV) and make data-driven decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using CRM and Customer Success platforms, such as Salesforce, HubSpot, Gainsight, or similar tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive mindset with a strong sense of ownership and urgency, focused on problem-solving and value creation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree completed, preferably in Business Administration, Marketing, Engineering, Communication, or related fields.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Availability for in-person client meetings, when necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent English proficiency:, Working with global clients or VTEX-related materials in English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preferred languages: Spanish, Italian, French &amp;amp; German are a not mandatory but desired&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
