&lt;h1&gt;About the Role&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Product Builder to join the Engage squad, responsible for the Data and Human Support products within the&amp;nbsp; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vtex.com/pt-br/products/cx_platform/&quot;&gt;VTEX CX Platform&lt;/a&gt;. This is a hands-on, high-ownership role for someone who thrives at the intersection of product, engineering, and design, and is passionate about building digital products that deliver measurable business and customer impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will lead the development of high-impact digital products with multidisciplinary teams, taking full ownership of operations, performance, and costs under a “you build it, you run it” mindset. We need someone who can connect vision to execution, make informed trade-offs, and drive initiatives independently in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will leverage AI and modern tooling to accelerate prototyping, documentation, API development, and task automation, while maintaining strong fluency with engineering and design teams to ensure agile, high-quality delivery. Strong cross-functional collaboration, execution excellence, and a product mindset focused on outcomes are essential for success in this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Key Responsabilities&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Define product vision, metrics, and strategy based on real customer problems, usage data, and market trends — leading lean discovery processes that validate hypotheses through rapid AI-powered prototyping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead a stream-aligned squad, prioritize the backlog, remove blockers, and act hands-on in the development, testing, and launch of high-value increments,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;using AI agents to orchestrate and accelerate execution across the cycle.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce requirements, diagrams, and documentation collaboratively and iteratively,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;with AI as a core accelerator&lt;/strong&gt; — reducing friction and keeping engineering, design, and data teams aligned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take full ownership of the product lifecycle (&quot;you build it, you run it&quot;),&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;leveraging AI-powered observability and automation&lt;/strong&gt; to monitor performance, costs, and reliability while driving continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate agile ceremonies (planning, daily stand-ups, reviews, retrospectives, and post-mortems) to promote transparency, continuous learning, and the delivery of tangible business value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Who you are&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–3+ years of experience in software development or in product roles within digital products, such as Product Manager, Technical Product Manager, Product Owner, or other positions embedded in software product teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Real AI fluency: acts as an agent orchestrator, decomposing problems, delegating to AI systems, and combining outputs to multiply productivity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on background in software environments, comfortable with APIs, technical documentation, and integration flows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to define product vision, set metrics, and translate strategy into an executable roadmap with autonomy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical fluency: comfortable reading API specs (REST, GraphQL, Webhooks), running basic SQL/NoSQL queries, and discussing architecture trade-offs with engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiar with agile methodologies and experienced with plannings, dailies, reviews, and retrospectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communicator: able to simplify technical concepts into clear narratives for both teams and stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable with product metrics and evidence-based decision making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
