&lt;h2&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VTEX is looking for a Senior Product Manager to lead the future of Content Management across our Commerce Platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is for product builders. We’re looking for someone who doesn’t just write specs and manage roadmaps, but someone who actively uses modern AI tools, rapid prototyping techniques, and emerging technologies to accelerate discovery, validation, and execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Product Manager for CMS, you will shape how brands, marketers, developers, and AI systems create, manage, and deliver digital experiences on VTEX. You will be responsible for defining the next generation of content management capabilities, helping customers move faster from idea to production while maintaining the flexibility and performance required by enterprise commerce. You will work at the intersection of commerce, content, AI, developer experience, and user experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success in this role requires strong product judgment, technical curiosity, and a passion for building. We expect you to be comfortable turning ideas into working prototypes, leveraging tools like Claude Code, Spec Kit, AI coding assistants, agents, MCP-based workflows, and other emerging technologies to validate solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a role for someone who believes the future of product management is increasingly hands-on and AI-native.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CMS team owns the systems that power content creation, collaboration, and delivery across storefronts. Our mission is to enable merchants to create rich, performant, and personalized digital experiences with speed and confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We build the experience that powers everything from landing pages and merchandising experiences to personalized content journeys and AI-assisted content operations. As commerce becomes increasingly AI-driven, the CMS team is at the forefront of defining how content, data, agents, and commerce workflows come together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team consists of product managers, engineers, and designers who care deeply about craft, experimentation, and customer impact. We value builders who are excited to challenge assumptions, prototype new ideas quickly, and leverage technology to create meaningful advantages for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;WHAT YOU WILL DO&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute the product strategy and roadmap for VTEX CMS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities where AI can fundamentally improve content creation, management, personalization, governance, and delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with engineering and design to build best-in-class content management experiences for enterprise commerce.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rapidly validate ideas through prototypes, proofs of concept, and experimentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage modern AI development workflows and tools to accelerate product discovery, specification, and validation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with customers to deeply understand content operations, publishing workflows, developer needs, and business challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive product decisions through a combination of customer insights, market research, experimentation, and data analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with platform teams to ensure CMS capabilities integrate seamlessly with storefront, search, merchandising, and commerce services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay at the forefront of AI, developer tooling, content management, and digital experience trends, identifying opportunities that create durable competitive advantages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define clear success metrics and continuously measure product impact, adoption, and customer outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence product direction across multiple teams and contribute to VTEX’s broader platform strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;WHO YOU ARE&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;

&lt;h2&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Senior Product Marketing Manager to drive go-to-market strategy across VTEX&#39;s platform portfolio. This is a builder&#39;s role: you set the strategy and execute it yourself, working at the center of product, growth, and sales in a fast-moving, global environment. You will define how we position our solutions, craft messaging that resonates with buyers, drive adoption across the existing VTEX customer base, and contribute to new customer acquisition.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need someone who takes ownership, drives initiatives independently, and can translate complex product capabilities into clear, compelling narratives. You will work closely with product managers, sales, and growth teams, so the ability to build trust quickly and drive alignment across teams, from regional sales to product leadership, without relying on formal authority is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join the Global Product Marketing team at VTEX, a high-performance group responsible for positioning our platform, enabling Sales and Partners, and driving category leadership across regions. We operate closely with Product, Sales, and Executive leadership, translating innovation into clear commercial narratives that drive growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;WHAT YOU WILL DO&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own positioning and messaging. &lt;/strong&gt;Build and maintain the positioning source of truth across VTEX&#39;s platform portfolio. Develop differentiated messaging for each solution tailored to target personas, markets, and industries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead go-to-market strategy and product launches. &lt;/strong&gt;Own end-to-end GTM planning, from aligning phased roadmaps with product teams to executing launches and enabling regional marketing, sales, and growth teams globally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Define the ICP and drive market intelligence. &lt;/strong&gt;Establish and refine the Ideal Customer Profile. Conduct ongoing competitive and market analysis to sharpen product differentiation and use data to inform strategic decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
