&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Senior Technical Product Manager to lead key initiatives within our Cloud &amp;amp; SRE organization. This role is critical to defining the long-term vision of our Core Infrastructure Platform, elevating reliability, efficiency, and Developer Experience (DevEx). You will work at the intersection of engineering, leadership, and product to transform complex infrastructure challenges into scalable solutions that directly impact cost-per-order and customer trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU WILL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and evolve the strategic vision for our Core Platform, expanding the management of critical resources such as RDS, SQS, and Serverless applications;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the vision for Safe Releases, integrating CI/CD, Feature Flags, and AI/ML for predictive analytics, anomaly detection, and automated orchestration;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the adoption of AI/ML to improve the software development lifecycle, focusing on automated setup (Golden Paths), documentation, and testing;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and implement a &quot;System Maturity&quot; model to help engineering teams prioritize non-functional initiatives (security, reliability, and efficiency) based on data-driven health metrics;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Redefine the FinOps solution vision to provide visibility into efficiency opportunities and reduce the infrastructure cost-per-order across the company;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Customer Excellence teams to translate internal observability metrics into external health dashboards, improving transparency and trust;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively participate in the Incident Lifecycle Program, using incidents as a source of truth to identify reliability gaps and roadmap opportunities;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct ongoing discovery to understand developer pain points through interviews, ceremony participation, and collaboration with technical leads;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shield engineering teams from unplanned demands, lead Quarterly Business Reviews (QBRs), and align the roadmap with executive leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO YOU ARE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in Software Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous hands-on experience as a Software Engineer is essential to understand our internal users&#39; challenges;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong track record as a Technical Product Manager in platform/infrastructure teams, with deep knowledge of Cloud, SRE, or DevOps environments;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to connect technical KPIs (MTTR, availability, latency) with business outcomes;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with FinOps, observability tools (e.g., Datadog, Grafana), and a strong interest in applying AI to improve engineering workflows;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in stakeholder management, with the ability to navigate complex technical discussions and executive alignments;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
